---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="safenpm — sandbox your package installs" description="Run npm/pnpm/yarn/bun install with bwrap sandboxing to keep secrets out of reach of postinstall scripts.">
  <header class="border-b border-zinc-800">
    <nav class="mx-auto flex max-w-5xl items-center justify-between px-4 py-4">
      <span class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight">safenpm</span>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/asmyshlyaev177/safenpm"
        class="rounded-lg bg-zinc-800 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium transition hover:bg-zinc-700"
      >
        GitHub
      </a>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <main>
    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 pt-24 pb-16 text-center">
      <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-6xl">
        Install packages.
        <span class="text-blue-500">Not threats.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="mx-auto mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg text-zinc-400">
        safenpm runs <code class="rounded bg-zinc-800 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-sm text-zinc-300">npm install</code>,
        <code class="rounded bg-zinc-800 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-sm text-zinc-300">pnpm add</code>, and friends inside a
        lightweight <strong class="text-zinc-200">bwrap</strong> sandbox &mdash; so your SSH keys,
        cloud credentials, and <code class="rounded bg-zinc-800 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-sm text-zinc-300">.env</code>
        files stay yours.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-10 flex items-center justify-center gap-4">
        <a
          href="#install"
          class="rounded-lg bg-blue-600 px-6 py-3 font-semibold transition hover:bg-blue-500"
        >
          Get started
        </a>
        <a
        href="https://github.com/asmyshlyaev177/safenpm"
          class="rounded-lg border border-zinc-700 px-6 py-3 font-semibold transition hover:bg-zinc-800"
        >
          View on GitHub &rarr;
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Motivation -->
    <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-16">
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-red-900/40 bg-red-950/20 p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-400">Why safenpm?</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed">
          In May&nbsp;2026 the <strong>TanStack supply-chain worm</strong> compromised 84 npm packages.
          Postinstall scripts exfiltrated CI/CD secrets, SSH keys, cloud credentials, and crypto wallets,
          and installed persistence hooks. The worm spread with valid SLSA Build&nbsp;Level&nbsp;3
          provenance, making it nearly indistinguishable from legitimate releases.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed">
          safenpm prevents this class of attack at the OS level &mdash; <strong>without</strong> requiring
          a per-package allowlist, without modifying your workflow, and with zero config in most cases.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- How it works -->
    <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center">How it works</h2>
      <div class="mt-10 grid gap-8 sm:grid-cols-3">
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900/50 p-6">
          <div class="flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-blue-600 text-lg font-bold">
            1
          </div>
          <h3 class="mt-4 font-semibold text-lg">Global shims</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
            One-line install puts lightweight shims on your PATH. When you run
            <code class="rounded bg-zinc-800 px-1 text-xs">npm install</code>,
            safenpm intercepts it automatically.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900/50 p-6">
          <div class="flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-blue-600 text-lg font-bold">
            2
          </div>
          <h3 class="mt-4 font-semibold text-lg">bwrap sandbox</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
            The install runs in a Bubblewrap container. Secrets in
            <code class="rounded bg-zinc-800 px-1 text-xs">~/.ssh</code>,
            <code class="rounded bg-zinc-800 px-1 text-xs">~/.aws</code>, and your environment are
            invisible to postinstall scripts.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900/50 p-6">
          <div class="flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-blue-600 text-lg font-bold">
            3
          </div>
          <h3 class="mt-4 font-semibold text-lg">Zero config</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
            Non-install commands pass through unchanged. No allowlists, no policy files, no daemon.
            Just sandboxed package management.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Install -->
    <section id="install" class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center">Install in one line</h2>
      <div class="mt-8 rounded-xl border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900 p-6">
        <code class="block text-sm text-green-400 leading-relaxed">
          curl -fsSL https://safenpm.dev/install.sh | sh
        </code>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-4 text-center text-sm text-zinc-500">
        Requires Linux with <code class="rounded bg-zinc-800 px-1 text-xs">bubblewrap</code>
        &nbsp;(<code class="rounded bg-zinc-800 px-1 text-xs">bwrap</code>) installed.
        macOS support via Docker.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Commands -->
    <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center">Then use your package manager as usual</h2>
      <div class="mt-8 grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900/50 p-6">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg">npm</h3>
          <code class="mt-3 block rounded-lg bg-zinc-950 p-4 text-sm text-zinc-300">
            npm install express
          </code>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900/50 p-6">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg">pnpm</h3>
          <code class="mt-3 block rounded-lg bg-zinc-950 p-4 text-sm text-zinc-300">
            pnpm add zod
          </code>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900/50 p-6">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg">yarn</h3>
          <code class="mt-3 block rounded-lg bg-zinc-950 p-4 text-sm text-zinc-300">
            yarn add react
          </code>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900/50 p-6">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg">bun</h3>
          <code class="mt-3 block rounded-lg bg-zinc-950 p-4 text-sm text-zinc-300">
            bun add @hono/hono
          </code>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <footer class="border-t border-zinc-800 px-4 py-8">
      <p class="text-center text-sm text-zinc-500">
        safenpm &mdash; MIT license. Built by
        <a href="https://github.com/asmyshlyaev177" class="underline hover:text-zinc-300">asmyshlyaev177</a>.
          <a href="https://asmyshlyaev177.dev" class="underline hover:text-zinc-300">asmyshlyaev177.dev</a>
      </p>
    </footer>
  </main>
</Layout>
